  <a rid="pone.0217608.ref042" ref-type="bibr" href="#pone.0217608.ref042">42</a>][
  <a rid="pone.0217608.ref043" ref-type="bibr" href="#pone.0217608.ref043">43</a>] The “right-facing megaphone” shape of polarization widening with education, as seen in 
  <a ref-type="fig" rid="pone.0217608.g010" href="#pone.0217608.g010">Fig 10A, 10B and 10D</a>, reflects a pervasive reality of current US politics.
 </p>
